* ============================================================
*  PINOCCHIO MEASURE -- timed query battery over the Pinocchio lane
*  CANDIDATE / REVIEW_BEFORE_EXECUTION. Read-only (no mutation).
*  SET TIMER ON makes the shell print elapsed per command -- that is the metric.
* ============================================================
SET ECHO OFF
SET TIMER ON

SET PATH DBF DBF/pinocchio
SET PATH INDEXES INDEXES/pinocchio
SET PATH LMDB LMDB/pinocchio

ECHO === 1. full scan throughput: COUNT ===
USE STUDENTS
SET INDEX TO STUDENTS
COUNT

ECHO === 2. canary + ordered top by SID (must read 50000000 Taylor Quinn) ===
SET ORDER TO TAG SID
TOP
SMARTLIST SID,LNAME,FNAME NEXT 5

ECHO === 3. ordered seek-to-top by LNAME (Anderson first) ===
SET ORDER TO TAG LNAME
TOP
SMARTLIST SID,LNAME,FNAME NEXT 20

ECHO === 4. predicate scan over 1M rows: LIST FOR MAJOR = CSCI ===
LIST FOR MAJOR = CSCI

ECHO === 5. point lookup lands: SEEK a known SID ===
SET ORDER TO TAG SID
SEEK 50000500
SMARTLIST SID,LNAME,FNAME NEXT 1

ECHO === 6. child ordered walk: ENROLL by SID (5-8M rows) ===
SELECT 1
USE ENROLL
SET INDEX TO ENROLL
COUNT
SET ORDER TO TAG SID
TOP
SMARTLIST SID,CLS_ID NEXT 10

ECHO === 7. child point lookup: SEEK a SID on ENROLL ===
SEEK 50000500
SMARTLIST SID,CLS_ID NEXT 8

ECHO ============================================================
ECHO MEASURE COMPLETE. Record each command's elapsed (SET TIMER ON).
ECHO Reject on: COUNT != generated N; canary not 50000000 Taylor Quinn;
ECHO   SMARTLIST out of tag order; any SEEK missing; a crash or truncation.
ECHO ============================================================
